## 1. Definitions

"Licensor" means Daniel Harding and RomanAILabs.

"Licensed Work" means the NRL machine-code engine, NrlPy Python front-end,
Bio-Digital Brain architecture, associated assembly kernels, compiler/runtime
components, scripts, examples, documentation, tests, model-object formats,
ZPM/LMO/WAL/pruning systems, algorithms, interfaces, APIs, file formats,
benchmarks, designs, diagrams, naming, and any other software, documentation,
or materials provided by RomanAILabs under this license.

"Evaluate" means to read, inspect, and run the Licensed Work locally on hardware
you control solely to understand its behavior and determine whether to request a
commercial license from RomanAILabs.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Licensed Work, any derivative work, or any
implementation of the Licensed Work's protected architecture, algorithms,
interfaces, or file formats:

- To provide a service, including SaaS, PaaS, hosted inference, hosted learning,
  hosted model orchestration, benchmarking-as-a-service, consulting, training,
  integration, or other compensated offerings.
- In any product, library, platform, application, derivative work, embedded
  system, internal tool, research program, or business process that is sold,
  licensed, rented, monetized, bundled, funded, deployed, or distributed for
  commercial advantage.
- For internal operations, product development, research and development,
  evaluation, benchmarking, or procurement by any for-profit entity, startup,
  partnership, government contractor, lab, fund, or affiliated organization.
- To train, operate, optimize, benchmark, validate, market, or provide a
  competing or substitute product, service, model-runtime system, or derivative.

"Competing Use" means using, studying, copying, modifying, translating,
benchmarking, analyzing, or implementing the Licensed Work, or any non-public or
public information derived from it, to build, improve, benchmark, operate,
market, fund, or provide a competing high-performance neural runtime, low-bit
compute fabric, lattice execution engine, GGUF/LMO/ZPM runtime, model-memory
system, neural acceleration service, hosted inference/learning service, or
substantially similar product, service, architecture, or research system.

